Place onion in 3 1/2- to 4-quart slow cooker. Place beef on onion, overlapping slightly. Add gravy mix and vegetable juice, making sure all of the gravy mix is moistened; cover. Cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours. Before serving, cook noodles according to package directions. Toss with butter and salt. Serve meat and sauce over noodles. Sprinkle with parsley.